when you were struggling.

26:30.646 --> 26:33.079
She could've buried that

26:33.110 --> 26:36.727
and the incident triggered
some repressed emotion.

26:39.126 --> 26:40.311
Listen, Beth, I,

26:41.751 --> 26:45.334
no, I think that Meg is
lucky to have you as a mom.

26:45.367 --> 26:46.742
I really do, I mean,
especially since you can

26:46.775 --> 26:49.014
understand what she's
going through right now.

26:50.710 --> 26:53.110
But you have to remember
that you're an example.

26:53.143 --> 26:55.671
You're an example
of how to be strong,

26:55.702 --> 26:58.262
an example of how to
recover from a tough time.

26:59.671 --> 27:00.502
Yeah.

27:02.487 --> 27:05.494
But to go back to
your original question,

27:06.487 --> 27:10.231
yeah, yeah, I do think that
the anxiety is getting worse.

27:11.414 --> 27:15.286
She understands the
idea of a worry monster

27:15.319 --> 27:17.526
and I think the coping
skills I'm teaching her

27:17.558 --> 27:19.734
are helping her get
through the school day but

27:20.758 --> 27:25.462
I'm gonna recommend a
psychiatrist outside of school.

27:26.582 --> 27:27.638
She's really good.

27:28.630 --> 27:31.543
And depending on what her
pediatrician says, it...

27:34.551 --> 27:37.974
It may be time for some
low grade medication.

27:38.006 --> 27:40.246
- No, I'm not...
- Listen, I understand.

27:40.279 --> 27:42.967
It's just, she just
may need a little help

27:42.998 --> 27:46.614
until she gets older and develops
more mature coping skills.

27:52.727 --> 27:55.607
So let's get her
back to class, huh?

27:57.334 --> 27:58.166
Okay.

27:59.222 --> 28:00.374
Hey, Meg.

28:00.407 --> 28:01.782
Meg, come on, come on.

28:04.791 --> 28:07.127
Well, we ran over
just a bit, didn't we?

28:07.159 --> 28:09.047
I actually have
to get to another student.

